<div class="header"><h1 property="headline">Tuvaluâ€™s former PM Sopoaga has another shot </h1></div><div class="column span-2"><p>
                
                
                By <em property="author">Robert Matau</em><br/></p><p><strong><a href="/web/20130921053304/http://www.islandsbusiness.com/news/">News</a></strong><br/><em property="datePublished">Mon 10 Jun 2013</em></p><dl><dt>Topics</dt><dd><a href="/web/20130921053304/http://www.islandsbusiness.com/topics/tuvalu/" property="articleSection">Tuvalu</a></dd></dl><dl><dt>Share this article</dt><dd><i class="icon-envelope"></i><a target="_blank" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053304/mailto:/?subject=Tuvalu%E2%80%99s%20former%20PM%20Sopoaga%20has%20another%20shot%20&amp;body=OPPOSITION%20leader%20Enele%20Sopoaga%E2%80%99s%20older%20brother%20Saufatu%20Sopoaga%20is%20one%20of%20three%20candidates%20nominated%20for%20the%20vacant%20Nukufetau%20seat%20by%20election%2C%20scheduled%20for%20June%2028.%20%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.islandsbusiness.com%2Fnews%2Ftuvalu%2F1437%2Ftuvalus-former-pm-sopoaga-has-another-shot%2F">Email</a></dd><dd><i class="icon-facebook-sign"></i><a target="_blank" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053304/https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?s=100&amp;p%5Burl%5D=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.islandsbusiness.com%2Fnews%2Ftuvalu%2F1437%2Ftuvalus-former-pm-sopoaga-has-another-shot%2F&amp;p%5Btitle%5D=Tuvalu%E2%80%99s%20former%20PM%20Sopoaga%20has%20another%20shot%20&amp;p%5Bsummary%5D=OPPOSITION%20leader%20Enele%20Sopoaga%E2%80%99s%20older%20brother%20Saufatu%20Sopoaga%20is%20one%20of%20three%20candidates%20nominated%20for%20the%20vacant%20Nukufetau%20seat%20by%20election%2C%20scheduled%20for%20June%2028.">Facebook</a></dd><dd><i class="icon-twitter-sign"></i><a target="_blank" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053304/https://twitter.com/intent/tweet/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.islandsbusiness.com%2Fnews%2Ftuvalu%2F1437%2Ftuvalus-former-pm-sopoaga-has-another-shot%2F&amp;text=Tuvalu%E2%80%99s%20former%20PM%20Sopoaga%20has%20another%20shot%20&amp;via=IslandsBusines">Twitter</a></dd></dl></div><div class="column last span-4" property="articleBody"><p>OPPOSITION leader Enele Sopoagaâ€™s older brother Saufatu Sopoaga is one of three candidates nominated for the vacant Nukufetau seat by election, scheduled for June 28.</p><p>Sopoaga and Elisala Pita were nominated by the Nukufetau community with a strong Opposition backing, and it is understood one of the candidates will withdraw their nomination during the withdrawal period.</p><p>Government has nominated career school teacher Petely Niuatui. She taught at Motufoua Secondary school and is now with the Foundation Unit of the University of the South Pacific in Tuvalu.</p><p>Pita has had a long and distinguished career with the Fisheries Department culminating in his being employed as a Fisheries Adviser with the USAID, then based in Suva. </p><p>At the end of his tenure with USAID, he returned to Tuvalu and became a Permanent Secretary for Natural Resources and Environment for several years, until he was elected to parliament in 2002 from Nukufetau. </p><p>He held his seat for two consecutive terms until he lost the elections in 2010 elections.</p><p>Saufatu Sopoaga was a career civil servant and retired from the civil service as the Secretary to Government,  the highest post in their civil service. </p><p>He was elected in 2000 and became Prime Minister, but their party was involved in a lot of internal squabbles and he lost his seat in the 2006 elections.</p><p>His younger brother Enele took over from him in the last general elections in 2010.</p><hr/><p><strong><a href="/web/20130921053304/http://www.islandsbusiness.com/news/">&laquo; View more Latest News stories</a></strong></p><p>...or view more articles related to these topics:</p><ul><li><a href="/web/20130921053304/http://www.islandsbusiness.com/topics/tuvalu/">Tuvalu</a></li></ul><p>...or try these related articles:</p><ul></ul></div></div><!-- Right utility column --><div class="column last span-3"><div class="ad module centre"><!-- IBI/Sidebar-MedRec --><div id="div-gpt-ad-1361875573780-5" style="width:30